title: With Oregon Ducks coming to town, Huskies hoping for first sellout at Husky Stadium in nearly two years
text:
With Oregon Ducks coming to town, Huskies hoping for first sellout at Husky Stadium in nearly two years Originally published October 15, 2015 at 2:51 pm Updated October 15, 2015 at 2:54 pm Fans cheer at kickoff as the University of Washington Huskies take on the Boise State Broncos for the first game in the new Husky Stadium on Aug. 31, 2013. (Bettina Hansen/The Seattle Times) Huskies have sold about 67,000 tickets for Saturday's game vs. the Ducks. By Adam Jude Seattle Times staff reporter 
Since the new $282-million Husky Stadium was unveiled at the start of the 2013 season, the Huskies have had just three sellouts in 18 home games. 
The last sellout? That was in the Apple Cup in 2013, nearly two years ago. 
Washington coach Chris Petersen has seen new Husky Stadium packed to the rafters … but that was for the 2013 season opener, when Petersen was coaching Boise State on the opponent’s sideline. 
The Huskies say they would love to see the stadium full when rival Oregon visits Saturday night (7:30 p.m., EPN2). As of Thursday morning, UW reported that a little under 67,000 tickets had been sold for the game. Most Read Stories
